%F A369891 a(2*k+1) <= a(2*k), because 2*k+1 squares of side 2*k+1 can be added in an L-shape to a square of side k*(2*k+1) to obtain a square of side (2*k+1)*(k+1).
%F A369891 a(n) = 0 if and only if A381976(n) > 0 or n = 0. - _Pontus von Brömssen_, Dec 09 2025
